pass ONLY_ACTIVE_ARCH=NO to xctool, hopefully this fixes `make test`

I don't fully understand _why_ this is needed.  I think it's a
shortcoming in xctool, but we don't have it figured out yet.

I find I have to add this whenever I'm running application tests.

'make test' should specify the iphonesimulator SDK for running tests.

Without this, we'll get the project default which is 'iphoneos' for ARM,
and then we won't be able to run the tests.

enable 'Find Implicit Dependencies' to make Tests run in Xcode

This fixes the random linker errors you see when doing Product -> Test
from Xcode.

Since 'Parallelize Build' was enabled, the order in which Xcode was
building the targets was non-deterministic.  Sometimes dependencies
would get built in the right order, but sometimes not.  The implicit
dependencies stuff sorts this out.
